ZH: 在学术论文中，常常会援引其他研究的结果。
EN: In academic papers, it is common to cite the results of other studies.

ZH: 他们援引了著名学者的观点来支持自己的论点。
EN: They cited the views of a famous scholar to support their argument.

ZH: 请在文中援引相关的案例以增加可信度。
EN: Please cite relevant cases in the article to enhance credibility.

ZH: 研究者应该遵守援引规范，确保学术诚信。
EN: Researchers should adhere to citation norms to ensure academic integrity.

ZH: 这篇文章援引了多篇先前的研究成果。
EN: This article cites the results of several previous studies.

ZH: 请确保在适当的地方援引原始资料。
EN: Please make sure to cite the primary sources in the appropriate places.

ZH: 他们总是援引同一个研究团队的发现。
EN: They always cite the findings of the same research team.

ZH: 援引国外研究成果有助于提升文章的国际化水平。
EN: Citing foreign research results helps to enhance the internationalization of the article.

ZH: 他的研究论文中援引了大量的文献资料。
EN: His research paper cites a large amount of literature.

ZH: 学术论文中援引合适的资料是十分重要的。
EN: It is crucial to cite appropriate sources in academic papers.

ZH: 在写作时不能随意援引他人的观点而不注明来源。
EN: When writing, one should not cite others' views arbitrarily without indicating the source.

ZH: 援引优秀学者的成果是我们进步的基石。
EN: Citing the achievements of outstanding scholars is the cornerstone of our progress.

ZH: 请在文中援引有关的统计数据。
EN: Please cite relevant statistical data in the article.

ZH: 在正式写作中援引必要的支持资料是必须的。
EN: It is necessary to cite the necessary supporting materials in formal writing.

ZH: 学者应该尊重他人的劳动成果，并合理援引。
EN: Scholars should respect the intellectual achievements of others and cite them properly.

ZH: 在讨论中，必须援引相关案例以支撑自己的观点。
EN: In the discussion, it is necessary to cite relevant cases to support one's point of view.

ZH: 援引不当有可能受到学术界的谴责。
EN: Improper citation may lead to condemnation from the academic community.

ZH: 致谢部分是文章中援引他人论点的必要环节。
EN: The acknowledgment section is a necessary part of citing others' arguments in the article.

ZH: 他的研究成果被广泛援引，成为同行们进一步研究的基础。
EN: His research results are widely cited and have become the basis for further research by peers.

ZH: 在作文中援引相关数据可以增加文章的可信度。
EN: Citing relevant data in an essay can increase the credibility of the article.
